, particularly in auditory hallucinations", "TEMPORAL LOBE EPILEPSY:", "TEMPORAL LOBE TUMOR:Tumors in the temporal lobe can cause temporal lobe epilepsy, behavioral and emotional changes, and symptoms like hallucinations, delusions, and intellectual deficits", "TENSION SYNDROME:Tension syndrome is a group of symptoms commonly seen in catatonic schizophrenia, characterized by increased muscle tension, including catatonic stupor and catatonic excitement.\"", "TESTOSTERONE:A hormone whose secretion is suppressed by long-term marijuana use, particularly in adolescents", "TETRAETHYL LEAD:An organic lead compound used as a gasoline additive, which is highly toxic and affects the central nervous system", "THALAMUS:The thalamus is a brain region involved in sensory and motor signal relay, and its anterior part has been studied in relation to aggressive and sexual behaviors in animals."], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}